---
source: src/tests.rs
expression: render_command_help(&refs)
---
Scroll an element into view

Usage: bl scroll into-view [OPTIONS] <selector>

Arguments:
  <selector>  CSS selector (or map ref) for the element to scroll into view

Options:
      --headless  Hide browser window (visible by default)
  -v, --verbose   Enable debug logging
      --json      Output as JSON
  -h, --help      Print help

Examples:
  bl scroll into-view "#footer"
  # Scroll the footer element into view (centered on screen)
